<text>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd">
&lt;html>&lt;head>&lt;meta name="qrichtext" content="1" />&lt;style type="text/css">
p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; }
&lt;/style>&lt;/head>&lt;body style=" font-family:'.SF NS Text'; font-size:13pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;">
&lt;p style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">“Being desirous… well-being of the native populations”&lt;/p>
&lt;p style=" margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">Here the crux of the Berlin Conference is laid bare for all to see. The conference had been prompted by the sudden emergence of a newly unified Germany as a player on the international, imperialistic stage. This text is framed as a way of preventing competition for African territories (&lt;span style=" font-weight:600;">the Scramble for Africa&lt;/span>) boiling over into armed or violent conflict. There is a token gesture made in consideration of the natives and their well-being at the end of this clause as well.&lt;/p>
&lt;p style="-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;">&lt;br />&lt;/p>&lt;/body>&lt;/html></text>
